### Models (7 new files)

Each model will be created via `php artisan make:model` with `--factory` and include:
- Fillable attributes
- Return-typed relationship methods
- Casts where needed

| Model | Key Relationships |
|---|---|
| `Sport` | `hasMany(Court)` |
| [Venue](file:///Users/alexjanuar/Projects/padel-reservation/resources/js/pages/Venue/Show.tsx#60-385) | `hasMany(Court)`, `belongsToMany(Facility)`, `hasMany(Review)` |
| `Facility` | `belongsToMany(Venue)` |
| `Court` | `belongsTo(Venue)`, `belongsTo(Sport)`, `hasMany(Booking)` |
| `Booking` | `belongsTo(User)`, `belongsTo(Court)`, `hasOne(Payment)` |
| `Payment` | `belongsTo(Booking)` |
| `Review` | `belongsTo(User)`, `belongsTo(Venue)` |

A `bookings()` relationship will also be added to the existing [User](file:///Users/alexjanuar/Projects/padel-reservation/app/Models/User.php#11-53) model.

---

### Factories & Seeders

- A factory for each model with realistic Indonesian data
- [DatabaseSeeder](file:///Users/alexjanuar/Projects/padel-reservation/database/seeders/DatabaseSeeder.php#9-24) will seed: 5 sports, 6 venues, ~20 facilities, ~15 courts, ~30 bookings, sample reviews
- Seeder data will match the mock data currently used in [welcome.tsx](file:///Users/alexjanuar/Projects/padel-reservation/resources/js/pages/welcome.tsx) and [Venue/Show.tsx](file:///Users/alexjanuar/Projects/padel-reservation/resources/js/pages/Venue/Show.tsx)

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

Run all tests:
```bash
php artisan test --compact
```

New tests to create:

1. **`tests/Feature/Models/SportTest.php`** — Verify `Sport` has courts relationship
2. **`tests/Feature/Models/VenueTest.php`** — Verify [Venue](file:///Users/alexjanuar/Projects/padel-reservation/resources/js/pages/Venue/Show.tsx#60-385) → courts, facilities, reviews relationships and computed average rating
3. **`tests/Feature/Models/BookingTest.php`** — Verify booking creation, status transitions, and the unique constraint preventing double-bookings

### Manual Verification

After seeding, verify the data looks correct:
```bash
php artisan migrate:fresh --seed
```
Then check the database has the expected records via tinker / the app UI.
